Package com.soprabanking.ips.models

Class Upvotes

java.lang.Object
com.soprabanking.ips.models.Upvotes
@Entity
public class Upvotes
extends java.lang.Object
Class representing an upvote made by a User on a given Proposal.Specifies all the fields and relationships of Upvote entity in the database.

A particular User can make only one upvote on a given Proposal by liking that Proposal.Once upvoted by a particular User,a particular Proposal cannot be reupvoted by the same User.A Proposal can have any number of upvotes.An upvote made by a particular User can be deleted either explicitly(User,who has liked the proposal,dislikes it) or implicitly(either User who has made the upvote is removed from the system or the Proposal for which upvote has been created is deleted from the database)

Author:
araghav
See Also:
User, Proposal
